  <p>Nice, capital of the French Riviera awaits you a quarter of an hour from the Mas du Chanoine. This cosmopolitan city will allow you to stroll, to go shopping, to visit museums.</p>
  <p>You can stroll on the very famous Promenade des Anglais and rest on its pretty sandy and pebble beaches, or organize your day according to a theme:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Visit of Old Nice in the morning and the very famous Cours Saleya market</li>
    <li>In the alleys of Old Nice, Lascaris Palace, churches, local crafts…</li>
    <li>General presentation of the city aboard the small tourist train</li>
    <li>More than ten museums: Matisse, Chagall, Asian Arts, Modern and Contemporary Art…</li>
    <li>Stroll through parks and gardens such as the Promenade du Paillon</li>
  </ul>
  <p>and many more according to your desires.</p>
